Wow this is great! Umbraco 5 keeps to amaze me :).

Can you use a partial view macro without creating a macro in the developer section? In 4.7 you can do this: &lt;umbraco:Macro runat=&quot;server&quot; FileLocation=&quot;~/macroScripts/Widgets.cshtml&quot; /&gt;

Jeroen

@Jeroen:
You just need to think outside the square that is Umbraco v4... Yes indeed you can run Partial View macros without creating a Macro in the back office... this is just a normal MVC Partial View! :)

Though, of course if you do that you wont be able to have Macro parameters injected into it from the Rich text editor.

